The paper deals with image denoising, which is a common problem in computer vision and image processing. The proposed method involves building a structural model for noisy patches and using a Bayesian nonparametric prior to control the complexity of the model. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of a mixture of Gaussian distribution and variational inference algorithm indicates that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information theory (cs.IT) sub-categories. Finally, the application of the proposed method on real noisy images suggests that the paper may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
